# Employee Payroll & Workforce Management System Rules

## Project Authority

Always follow:

1. PROJECT_MASTER_SPEC.md
2. DATABASE_SCHEMA.md
3. SYSTEM_ARCHITECTURE.md
4. PROJECT_STRUCTURE.md
5. Module Pseudocode Documents

If conflicts occur:

Pseudocode
>
Master Spec
>
Database Schema
>
Architecture

Never invent new business rules.

---

## Roles

System supports only:

ADMIN
HR
EMPLOYEE

No additional roles allowed.

---

## Authentication

Use:

Spring Security
JWT Authentication
Role Based Authorization

No Session Authentication.

---

## Employee Management

No Employee Delete.

No HR Delete.

Only Deactivate.

Employee IDs:

EMP001
EMP002
EMP003

Never Reuse.

HR IDs:

HR001
HR002
HR003

Never Reuse.

---

## Attendance

One Check-In Per Day.

One Check-Out Per Day.

Statuses:

PRESENT
ABSENT
LEAVE
HALF_DAY_LEAVE

Saturday and Sunday:

Holiday.

---

## Leave

Annual Paid Leave:

Read From System Settings.

Leave Types:

CASUAL
SICK
UNPAID

Approval:

Employee → HR

HR → ADMIN

---

## Payroll

Formula:

Final Salary =
Basic Salary
+ Bonus
- PF
- Unpaid Leave Deduction

PF Percentage:

Read From System Settings.

Payroll Generation
≠
Salary Credit.

Salary Credit:

Manual Action.

---

## Payslip

Generated Automatically.

PDF Only.

Use Payroll Snapshot Data.

Never Recalculate Salary.

---

## Reports

PDF Only.

Use Shared Summary Services.

Dashboard Totals
=
Report Totals

---

## Notifications

Bell:

Latest 10 Notifications.

History:

30 Days.

Notifications are event driven.

---

## System Settings

Single Settings Record.

Never Delete.

Only Admin Can Manage.

---

## Backend Rules

Architecture:

Controller
→ Service
→ Repository

Never skip layers.

Use DTOs.

Use Mappers.

Business Logic belongs only in Service Layer.

---

## Frontend Rules

React + Vite

Role Based Layouts:

AdminLayout

HRLayout

EmployeeLayout

Use Protected Routes.

Never hardcode API URLs.

Use service layer.

---

## Database Rules

Use MySQL.

Use snake_case columns.

Use soft delete via status fields.

No physical delete for employees or HR.

---

## Development Rules

Implement one module at a time.

Complete Backend First.

Then Frontend.

Then Testing.

Never redesign project architecture.

Never create new modules.

Follow pseudocode exactly.

When uncertain:
Ask before changing business logic.

## Profile Pictures

Store files in:

backend/uploads/profile/

Database stores only:

profile_photo_url

Allowed Formats:

JPG
JPEG
PNG

Maximum Size:

2 MB

Users may update only their own profile photo.